import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="job", y="count", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Job', ylabel='Count')
    ax.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('sex').sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.pie(data['count'], labels=data['sex'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=['#ff9999','#66b3ff'])
    ax.set_title('How does the count of males and females compare in the dataset?')
    ax.legend(title='Sex', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    ax = sns.lineplot(x="year", y="count", data=data, color='blue')
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Count')
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over the years in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.catplot(x="job", y="count", hue="sex", data=data, kind="bar", height=6, aspect=1.5)
    chart.set_xticklabels(rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('How does the count of males and females vary across job categories in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Sex', loc='upper right', labels=['Female', 'Male'])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
